   "source": [
    "### Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "The within-band test is the key diagnostic for residual outcome signal. If triage-time features contained meaningful information beyond the acuity label, then models trained separately within acuity bands 3 and 4 should perform above chance when predicting admission/transfer or long ED stay.\n",
    "\n",
    "In the synthetic benchmark, they do not. The within-band ROC-AUC values are clustered around the chance-level reference of **0.50**, ranging from **0.473** to **0.500** across the four outcome-band tests. Average precision is also approximately equal to each band’s outcome base rate. Together, these results indicate that, once acuity band is fixed, the available triage-time features do not meaningfully rank patients by outcome.\n",
    "\n",
    "This supports the severity-collapse interpretation for the synthetic dataset. The benchmark appears to separate risk mainly **between** acuity levels, rather than preserving reliable residual risk structure **within** them. For that reason, a within-band Triage Gap Index is not constructed on the synthetic data; the diagnostic does not provide enough residual signal for such an index to exploit.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
