   "source": [
    "### Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "MIMIC-IV-ED strengthens the real-data replication because it uses real ESI acuity rather than an acuity analogue. The strict triage-time model outperforms the ESI acuity-only baseline, and residual within-band signal remains visible inside ESI levels 3 and 4.\n",
    "\n",
    "This result challenges the synthetic **NO_SIGNAL** finding. In the synthetic benchmark, once acuity was fixed, triage-time features provided little residual outcome discrimination. In MIMIC-IV-ED, however, patients within the same ESI band can still be meaningfully ranked by admission/transfer and long-stay risk using triage-time features.\n",
    "\n",
    "This supports the interpretation that the synthetic **NO_SIGNAL** result reflects the structure of the benchmark rather than a general property of emergency triage data. The result does not clinically validate a deployment system, but it provides real-data evidence that triage-time information can preserve residual outcome signal beyond the acuity label.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
